00:04:54.030 --> 00:04:55.990
And so there's two ways,
and two ways, and two

00:04:55.990 --> 00:04:56.560
ways, and two ways.

00:04:56.560 --> 00:04:58.330
And you times them together.

00:04:58.330 --> 00:05:02.950
And because there's 12 edges
altogether, there are 2

00:05:02.950 --> 00:05:04.480
to the power 12.

00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:08.110
ADAM HADASH: 3, 2, 1.

00:05:10.930 --> 00:05:12.750
MATT PARKER: These two corners
are where I want them, but

00:05:12.750 --> 00:05:14.300
these two are the wrong
way around.

00:05:14.300 --> 00:05:18.320
And so I know if I do that,
that, that, that, that, that,

